description: Continued fraction for fifth root of 5.
comments: Fifth root of 5 = 5^(1/5). - _Harry J. Smith_, May 10 2009
references: H. P. Robinson, Letter to N. J. A. Sloane, Nov 13 1973.
N. J. A. Sloane and Simon Plouffe, The Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences, Academic Press, 1995 (includes this sequence).

prog: (PARI) { allocatemem(932245000); default(realprecision, 21000); x=contfrac(5^(1/5)); for (n=1, 20000, write("b002951.txt", n, " ", x[n])); } \\ _Harry J. Smith_, May 10 2009
